    </div>
    @if (ShowNotes)
    {
        <div
            class="speaker-notes w-full max-w-7xl mt-8 p-6 bg-white border-t-4 border-blue-500 rounded-lg shadow-xl text-left overflow-y-auto max-h-64">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Speaker Notes</h2>
            <div class="prose max-w-none text-gray-700">
                <p>Our final topic is Data Binding. This is a key feature of all modern UI frameworks. It's the mechanism
                    that automatically connects your UI to your data.</p>
                <p>Without data binding, a developer would have to write extra code to read a value from a variable and show
                    it in a textbox, and then more code to update the variable when the user types. Data binding does this
                    automatically.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    }
</div>
@code {
    [Parameter] public bool ShowNotes { get; set; } = false;
}